    "body": "I experimented with the following rule but it turns out to be very annoying in certain situations. Even though the types are declared in interfaces, we need to rewrite them every time. IMO we shouldn't go with this rule for now.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"typedef\": [true, \"call-signature\", \"property-declaration\"]\r\n```",
